Background

		Mr. James D. Wiggins, also known as Jim, serves as the President of STC Seller, Inc. Mr. Wiggins is an Operating Partner at Kohlberg & Company, L.L.C. since 2002 Mr. Wiggins joined Kohlberg & Company in 1996. He is responsible for investment thesis development, company diligence and portfolio management in the Industrial sector. In 2002, he joined Pittsburgh Glass Works L.L.C. and Stanadyne Corporation. He was the Chairman and Chief Executive Officer at Pittsburgh Glass ... Works L.L.C. Mr. Wiggins served as the Chief Executive Officer and President of Holley Performance Products, Inc. since July 20, 2002 and has been its Chairman since April 16, 2001. Previously, he served in a variety of senior management positions at the division, group and corporate levels. He served as an Executive Officer of Pinafore Holdings B.V. until May 27, 2002. Mr. Wiggins served as the Group President of the Stant-Schrader Group of the Gates Group of Companies from 1998 to 2000 and served as the President and Chief Executive Officer at the Gates Group, from 2000 to 2002. He served as the President and Chief Executive Officer of Schrader-Bridgeport International, Inc. (AKA Schrader International, Inc.) from 1996 to 1998. Mr. Wiggins served as the President and Chief Executive Officer of Bridge Products, Inc. He also served as an Artillery Officer in the United States Marine Corps. Mr. Wiggins served as the Chairman at Stanadyne Holdings Inc and Stanadyne Corporation, since August 6, 2004 and serves as its Director. He has been a Director of Holley Performance Products Inc. since 1998. He serves as the Chairman of Trico Products Corporation. Mr. Wiggins has an MBA from the Ball State University and a BS in Mechanical Engineering from Lawrence Technological University.Read Full Background




