James A. Kohlberg  Chairman, Essential Entertainment Media, L.L.C.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 12 Board Members in 12 different organizations across 13 different industries.See Board Relationships59--
Background

		Mr. James A. Kohlberg, also known as Jim, is the Co-founder and Chairman of Kohlberg Ventures LLC since 2008 and also serves as its Investment Partner. He is involved in identifying, evaluating and making investments. He has been investing in early stage media, entertainment, internet, specialty consumer products and healthcare companies for over 10 years. He co-founded ClearEdge Power, Inc., in 1987 and served as its Chairman of the Board from 2014 to 2015. He co-founded ... Kohlberg & Company, L.L.C. in 1987 and worked at its five previous funds and oversaw all of its investment activities since 1994. He was Managing Partner of Kohlberg & Company from 1993 to 2007 and serves as its Chairman since 2007. He gave majority of his time to outside activities, which include investing and overseeing a portfolio of venture capital investments in media related and clean-tech companies, film production and non-profit initiatives. Mr. Kohlberg has been a Co-Founder and Chairman of Halogen Media Networks (d/b/a Social Chorus) since 2007. He served as Vice President and Vice Chairman of KCAP Financial, Inc. He served as Managing Partner of Southwest Supermarkets, L.L.C (also known as Southwest Supermarkets Inc.) and is currently its Director. He served as an Executive Officer of Kohlberg Kravis Roberts & Co. from 1984 to 1987 and was involved in a number of buyout transactions including those of Safeway Stores and Red Lion Inns. Prior to this, he served at Merrill Lynch & Co. He serves as the Chairman of Essential Entertainment Media, L.L.C. He serves as Chairman of the Board of SocialChorus, Inc. He has also been a Director at The New York Times Company since April 2008; Color Spot Nurseries Inc. since December 1996 and Holley Performance Products Inc. since 1998. He serves as a Director of Troon Golf, Open Road Integrated Media Inc., AGY Holdings Corporation, SVP Holdings, Ltd., Simplicity Manufacturing Inc., Allied Aerospace Engineering, Inc., Applied Graphics Technologies, Inc., CUSA Busways, L.L.C., BI Incorporated, Invisible Technologies, Hot Stuff Foods, L.L.C., Singer WorldwideInc., Innotek, Inc., Nancy's Specialty Foods, Inc., Nevamar Company, L.L.C., Orion Food Systems, L.L.C., and KTTI Holding Company, Inc. He served as Director of KCAP Financial, Inc. from December 2006 to June 24, 2008. He served as Director of Seven Worldwide, Inc. since August 4, 2003; Katy Industries Inc. from 2001 to March 2007, Stanadyne Holdings, Inc. and Stanadyne Corp from August 6, 2004 to January 22, 2007, Camber Companies L.L.C., Printing Arts America LLC., and United Signature Foods, Inc. He served as a Member of the Board of Directors of ABT Building Products Corporation since joining in October 1992. He served as a Director of Northwestern Steel & Wire. He served as a Director of AviStar. He served as Chairman of Halogen Network. Mr. Kohlberg has over 20 years of experience in the buyout profession. Mr. Kohlberg has an M.B.A. from New York University and a B.A. from Golden Gate University.Read Full Background




